The location was excellent for us - near a vaporetto stop and the train station, in a quiet area of Santa Croce not too near the San Marco tourist mayhem.	The hotel is located in a very quiet part of Venice, about a 15-minute walk from the train station and a 15 to 20 minute walk to Plaza San Marco.	The location was great for us, as it was quiet, but at the same time an easy walk to St Mark's Sq, or the Vaporetto, and there are a couple of nice restaurants in the area (avoid Captains Cabin though!).